# Setup Manual Maintenance Rule

Use `doc/setup-manual.qmd` as the source of truth for environment and toolchain setup.

## End-of-step checklist (run before completing any substantial work step)

- Check whether changes affect environment prerequisites, toolchains, package managers, scripts, or setup commands.
- If yes, update `doc/setup-manual.qmd` in the same step:
  - Update "Last updated" date.
  - Update prerequisites and install steps.
  - Update runnable setup scripts and verification commands.
- Verify setup commands still match current repository layout and scripts.
- If setup impact is none, explicitly confirm no setup-manual update is required.

## Documentation discipline

- Keep setup steps copy-paste ready and platform-scoped when needed.
- Reference setup instructions from other manuals instead of duplicating them.
